About the job
Entry-Level Quality Assurance Engineer – Role Description & Qualifications
The Entry-Level Quality Assurance Engineer will support the delivery of high-quality software by ensuring applications meet defined requirements and standards. The role involves working closely with developers, product managers, and other stakeholders to understand system functionality and identify potential issues. Responsibilities include designing and executing test cases, documenting defects, performing manual and basic automated testing, and verifying bug fixes. The engineer will also assist in maintaining test documentation, improving testing processes, and ensuring consistent quality across releases. Attention to detail and a proactive approach are essential in identifying risks and contributing to overall product reliability.
Key qualifications include a foundational understanding of software testing principles, including functional, regression, and usability testing. Familiarity with testing tools, basic scripting, and bug-tracking systems is expected. The ideal candidate demonstrates strong analytical thinking, problem-solving skills, and the ability to communicate findings clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders. A structured and detail-oriented mindset, along with the ability to manage multiple tasks, is essential. Understanding of software development lifecycles, version control systems, and basic automation concepts is a plus. A willingness to learn, adapt, and continuously improve testing practices is highly valued.

