As an Automation Developer, you will play a key role in designing, developing, and supporting automated solutions that enhance Service Stream’s operational efficiency and system performance. You will take end\u2011to\u2011end ownership of automation workflows—delivering reliable, scalable, and well\u2011governed solutions that align with business needs and technical standards. Working closely with stakeholders across the organisation, you will help drive optimisation, integration, and continuous improvement initiatives within our automation capability.

This is a permanent, full\u2011time position based in our Melbourne office, with flexibility to consider candidates located in Brisbane or Sydney. The role supports hybrid working arrangements. Please note that this position is open only to Australian citizens.

About the role
• Design, develop, test, and deploy automation workflows, scripts, and system integrations across approved automation platforms.
• Manage full lifecycle ownership of automation solutions, including build, deployment, monitoring, and ongoing support.
• Engage directly with business stakeholders to gather requirements, translate needs into technical solutions, and communicate progress and risks.
• Implement robust system integrations using REST APIs and best\u2011practice data exchange patterns.
• Optimise automation workflows for reliability, maintainability, reusability, and performance.
• Investigate and resolve incidents, defects, and enhancement requests, including performing impact assessments.
• Produce and maintain high\u2011quality documentation in line with governance, standards, and delivery frameworks.
• Provide guidance and knowledge sharing to junior developers within the Automation Team.

Skills and experience
• Must be an Australian Citizen.
• Proven hands\u2011on experience across automation platforms such as Safe Software FME and Microsoft Power Automate.
• Strong scripting capability in Python, SQL, and PowerShell.
• Experience integrating systems using REST APIs and reusable integration components.
• Confident use of Git or similar version control tools, including branching, pull requests, and code reviews.
• Strong analytical, problem\u2011solving, and critical thinking skills.
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to work effectively with technical and non\u2011technical stakeholders.
• Experience working within Agile or Scrum development environments.

Qualifications
• Tertiary qualification in science, mathematics, engineering, information technology, or a related discipline, or equivalent experience.
• Relevant certifications highly regarded, including:
– FME Certified Professional
– Power Platform Developer Associate
• Experience applying Agile and DevOps methodologies.

