About the job
About Us

At Officeworks we make bigger things happen. Our customers, our team, and our community are our heart and soul. And if our brilliant people have taught us anything, it is that we can do all kinds of incredible things, each and every day.Fast paced. Innovative. Inspiring. With close to 10,000 team members and a national footprint of more than 173 retail stores Australia wide – we’re focused on delivering a wide range, low price and great service. We’re about inspiring new ideas and thinking outside the box. We’re about kicking goals, having a laugh and pushing each other. We are about being rewarded and supported. We’re about teaching a customer something new and supporting the community. We’re about making a difference.

About The Role

We are looking for an experienced AI Agent Trainer to design, build and optimise intelligent AI agents that can solve complex business problems. You have built agentic capability in the context of large organisations with large data sets and security requirements.

In this hands-on role, you will develop agentic AI systems by designing their reasoning, planning and decision-making capabilities, while shaping behaviours through data curation, fine-tuning and oversight. You’ll work in a small, highly collaborative team alongside the AI Integration Engineer and AI Product Innovation Lead to translate strategic opportunities into working prototypes and innovative AI-powered solutions.

Your focus will be on building intelligent agents that can interact with tools, data sources and systems to deliver measurable business outcomes and enable the organisation to become a more efficient, high-productivity retailer.

What You’ll Do

 Design and develop agentic AI prototypes and MVPs, focusing on rapid experimentation and proof of concept development, and taking them all the way to production 
 Build and refine AI agents’ reasoning, planning and decision-making capabilities, shaping how they operate and respond. 
 Curate datasets and fine-tune models to improve agent behaviour, reliability and performance. 
 Develop tools and APIs that enable AI agents to interact with internal systems, databases, and external services. 
 Implement agent-to-agent communication protocols and orchestrate multi-agent workflows. 
 Build observability and traceability systems to monitor agent decision-making and support debugging and optimisation. 
 Research and experiment with new AI models, agent frameworks and emerging technologies to keep innovation at the forefront. 
 Ensure solutions are designed with performance, scalability, security and ethical guardrails in mind. 


About You

You are a highly technical AI engineer who enjoys building intelligent systems from the ground up. You’re curious, innovative and comfortable experimenting with emerging technologies while solving complex real-world problems.

You thrive in small teams where collaboration, experimentation and rapid iteration drive innovation.

To Succeed In This Role, You Will Also Bring

 Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering or related discipline 
 Engineering experience with a strong technical portfolio 
 Proven experience designing and implementing AI-agentic systems or machine learning solutions 
 Strong Python programming skills 
 Experience with AI/ML frameworks such as LangChain, LlamaIndex, TensorFlow, PyTorch or Scikit-learn 
 Experience building APIs and integrating AI systems with external tools and services 
 Experience working with relational and non-relational databases 
 Expereince would be an advantage with cloud platforms such as AWS or Google Cloud 
 Experience working in innovation, startup, or fast-moving technical environments is highly regarded. 


,

Our culture

Benefits

If you’re searching for an organisation that’s truly committed to its people, where you can thrive in a culture of togetherness, then join Officeworks and let’s make bigger things happen – for all of us! We celebrate our teams’ uniqueness by offering genuine team member benefits to the Officeworks family:

 We’re all about giving you the flexibility you need to keep things balanced to suit your individual needs. 
 Enjoy generous discounts across Officeworks, Geeks2U, Bunnings, Kmart, Target and the wider Wesfarmers brands. 
 Access to our Officeworks benefits program for exclusive discounts and perks across entertainment, travel, lifestyle, and health. 
 Our Growing Families Policy supports team members during the exciting and challenging times of expanding their family 
 We prioritise safety, mental health and wellbeing, offering access to our Employee Assistance Program (EAP) as well as other ongoing programs 
 OurFlexible Public Holidays Policy supports those who observe cultural or religious holidays different from the standard public holidays in Australia 
 Take advantage of outstanding learning and development programs to support your career growth 
 Explore fantastic career opportunities across the broader Wesfarmers Group. 


At Officeworks, we operate best when our team represents the communities we serve. We proudly commit to providing a safe and supportive work environment for our team. We encourage applications from all candidates of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), people with disabilities, and the LGBTQI+ community.

